column1: Atmospheric CO2 concentrations (ppm) derived from continuous analyzer
near Point Barrow, Alaska by John Kelley in collaboration with C. D. Keeling
Source: R. F. Keeling, S. C. Piper, A. F. Bollenbacher and S. J. Walker
Scripps CO2 Program ( http://scrippsco2.ucsd.edu )
Scripps Institution of Oceanography (SIO)
University of California
La Jolla, California USA 92093-0244
Status of data and correspondence:
These data are subject to revision based on recalibration of standard gases
and re-evaluation of the carrier gas effect. Questions
about the data should be directed to Dr. Stephen Piper (scpiper@ucsd.edu) or
Dr. Ralph Keeling (rkeeling@ucsd.edu) of the Scripps CO2 Program
Please cite as:
Kelley, J.J., Jr. 1969.  An analysis of carbon dioxide in the arctic atmosphere near
Barrow, Alaska, 1961 to 1967, Scientific report, Department of Atmospheric
Sciences, University of Washington, Office of Naval Research, Contract
Date and Time are local times ('L'), given both in decimal and year, month, day form
Sample values are daily averages for all conditions.  Data have not been filtered for
wind direction or wind speed. Average time of day was not
saved in the original documentation and is listed as 9999L
Decimal date is calculated assuming noon time sample.
Pressure of -999 indicates ground-based measurement
Station KL1 (Kelley 1) was located on the ocean beach.  KL2 was located
1.2 km inland from the ocean near a lake at North Meadow station, as shown in figure 1
of Kelley, 1969
Data from KL1 were analyzed with an Applied Physics Corporation (APC) analyzer similar to
that used at Scripps whereas those at KL2 were analyzed with a URAS analyzer.  In this
data version, we have assumed that the carrier gas effect of the URAS was the same
as for the APC analyzer.
CO2 concentrations are expressed on the Scripps '08A' calibration scale (column 'CO2')
corrected for carrier gas, sample pressure, plenum volume change, flask size, and
analyzer detector changes
File is sorted by ascending date.
Flags:
0 - accepted value, continuous analyzer
5 - rejected value, more than 3 sigma from fitted spline curve
